- The Intel oneAPI Base and HPC Toolkits can be downloaded here:
- https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/tools/oneapi/base-toolkit-download.html
- https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/tools/oneapi/hpc-toolkit-download.html
- Make sure that the download options "Linux" and "Offline Installer" are highlighted before downloading.
- Note that ifort has been removed from the 2025 HPC Toolkit and replaced with ifx (LLVM).
- The 2024 version contains both ifort and ifx.
- The 2024 versions can be downloaded with these commands:
wget https://registrationcenter-download.intel.com/akdlm/IRC_NAS/e6ff8e9c-ee28-47fb-abd7-5c524c983e1c/l_BaseKit_p_2024.2.1.100_offline.sh
wget https://registrationcenter-download.intel.com/akdlm/IRC_NAS/d461a695-6481-426f-a22f-b5644cd1fa8b/l_HPCKit_p_2024.2.1.79_offline.sh
- Create an installation base directory and cd into it:
mkdir -p ${HOME}/intel/oneapi
cd $HOME/intel/oneapi
- Assuming your browser download location is "Downloads", install the 2025 Toolkits (or substitute with the 2024 ones) like this:
chmod a+x ${HOME}/Downloads/intel-oneapi-base-toolkit-2025.2.0.592_offline.sh
~/Downloads/intel-oneapi-base-toolkit-2025.2.0.592_offline.sh -a --silent --action install --eula accept --install-dir=${HOME}/intel/oneapi/ --ignore-errors
chmod a+x ${HOME}/Downloads/intel-oneapi-hpc-toolkit-2025.2.0.575_offline.sh
~/Downloads/intel-oneapi-hpc-toolkit-2025.2.0.575_offline.sh -a --silent --action install --eula accept --install-dir=${HOME}/intel/oneapi/ --ignore-errors
- Activate the Intel oneAPI environment
source $HOME/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh
- Optionally disable telemetry
echo "0.0.0.0 analytics.softwareimprovement.intel.com" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts
- Download and install OpenMPI
wget https://download.open-mpi.org/release/open-mpi/v5.0/openmpi-5.0.8.tar.gz
tar -xzf openmpi-5.0.8.tar.gz
cd openmpi-5.0.8
./configure CC=icx CXX=icpx FC=ifx F77=ifx --prefix=$HOME/openmpi-intel
- Or this for the 2024 version:
./configure CC=icx CXX=icpx FC=ifort F77=ifort --prefix=$HOME/openmpi-intel
make -j$(nproc)
make install
- Add OpenMPI paths to enviroment:
echo 'export PATH=$HOME/openmpi-intel/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/openmpi-intel/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
